Nelson Mandela Bay Ward 20 councillor Bongo Nombiba has been found guilty of fraud and money laundering in the Port Elizabeth Commercial Crimes Court. Nombiba was acquitted of two charges of corruption. He was arrested by the Hawks in 2016 and charged with fraud, corruption and contravening the Prevention of Organised Crime Act. Councillor on fraud charges to learn fate  A Nelson Mandela Bay councillor who allegedly swindled the municipality out of R20 000 is expected to learn his fate next week when the Port Elizabeth Commercial Crimes Court hands down judgment. In stark contrast to previous appearances, ANC Ward 20 councillor Bongo Nombiba had no supporters during closing arguments… March 1, 2018 A Port Elizabeth court was not big enough to accommodate the busload of ANC supporters dropped off yesterday to support Ward 20 councillor Bongo Nombiba when he appeared on a charge of fraud. Nombiba is accused of pocketing the bulk of the money meant for the Thulamangwane Community Project, a… January 27, 2017 ANC man accused of pocketing R20 000 from special metro fund A Nelson Mandela Bay ward councillor allegedly swindled the municipality out of R20 000, which was part of a donation to an organisation caring for the elderly. Ward 20 (Kwazakhele) ANC councillor Bongo Nombiba was arrested by the Hawks… December 13, 2016